  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global Water initiative East Africa: Water for Agriculture</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Smallholder farmers will achieve greater food security through more sustainable access and productive use of water</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Smallholder women farmers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Use of champion farmers to conduct training, demonstrate best or appropriate techniques and outreach to influence other farmers in the communities to adopt the techniques.
Use Learning and Practice Alliance model to involve key players of the project to promote and implement the program initiatives. The idea here is capitalizing the existing skills and experience that different stakeholders have. Also, this is to working with people from very different backgrounds, experiences and expertise on task-planning, problem solving, undertaking research, documenting findings, developing and implementing advocacy work plans.
Establish and use learning hub at national level to influence changes in strategy, planning, policy and budget for agriculture sector to increase investments in water for smallholder agriculture in Tanzania. This is a platform for sharing lessons and experiences.</narrative>
  </description>
